<TITLE> PM eyes German market for drugs </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 28 (bdnews24.com)Prime minister Sheikh Hasina invited German businessmen and entrepreneurs on Wednesday to import medicine and ceramic products from Bangladesh and invest in the country. The businessmen expressed keen interest in energy and telecoms sectors, the prime minister's press secretary Abul Kalam Azad said after she met with a German delegation. Peter Clasen, member of the OAV-German Asia Pacific Business Association Board and chairman of OAV's Bangladesh committee, led an eight-member delegation. German ambassador Holger Michael was also present during the meeting. The prime minister said the government was undertaking measures to encourage foreign investment. She pointed out, "Bangladesh now exports ships to Europe." Hasina also informed the representatives that the country's major rivers have been brought under a massive capital dredging programme as part of Bangladesh's efforts to fight effects of climate changes. The German team said that business and commerce was advancing in Bangladesh, Azad told reporters. "The representatives expressed their intention of investing in Bangladesh; they said their interest was increasing by the day." They expressed special interest to invest in Dhaka and Chittagong, said Azad. "The delegation also informed prime minister of their experience in coal mining and their interest to invest in solar and other renewable energy." Azad said the delegation was looking too at gas exploration in Bangladesh. They are also interested to invest in communications, and want to support agricultural development by training farmers in new technologies, he said. bd
